GENERATED ANSWER:
The answer was found in the provided sources. According to the ZDDV-1 rulebook (article 142.a člen, chunk_000228), a taxable person under ZDDV-1 is a taxpayer identified for VAT purposes under the fourth paragraph of article 78 of ZDDV-1, who performs services for which the recipient of the services is obliged to pay VAT in another EU member state.

